This paper presents a new framework for policy learning that leverages predictive models to accelerate learning. The paper discusses the development of a novel reduction from predictable online learning to adversarial online learning, which is likely to fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the application of the framework to robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.RO, cs.SY (systems and control), and cs.CV.
